<subSubSection id="C37665306A02FFCF04BBFF50C879290E" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BD336BB6A02FFCF04BBFF50C81C2AC1" blockId="6.[983,1326,192,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">
<heading id="D09B81D76A02FFCF04BBFF50C81C2AC1" bold="true" centered="true" fontSize="10" level="2" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" reason="2">
<emphasis id="B918EAA96A02FFCF04BBFF50C81C2AC1" bold="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">
Subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D386A02FFCF0307FF50C9232AC1" authority="Papa" authorityName="Papa" class="Insecta" family="Helotrephidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Trephotomasinae">Trephotomasinae Papá</taxonomicName>
ek, Štys &amp; Tonner, 1988
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD336BB6A02FFCF041AFEB0C879290E" blockId="6.[835,1475,288,823]" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">
At present, the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D386A02FFCF032AFEB0C8062B0E" box="[1139,1332,288,311]" class="Insecta" family="Helotrephidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Trephotomasinae">Trephotomasinae</taxonomicName>
is unknown from the study area. It is here included because the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D386A02FFCF041AFEF0C9612B4E" authority="Zettel, 2005" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2005" box="[835,1107,352,375]" class="Insecta" family="Helotrephidae" genus="Platytrephes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B918EAA96A02FFCF041AFEF0CEFB2B4E" box="[835,969,352,375]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">Platytrephes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B4A6A02FFCF0488FEF0C9612B4E" author="Zettel, H" box="[977,1107,352,375]" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" pagination="67 - 80" refId="ref6180" refString="Zettel, H., 2005. Notes on the Helotrephini (Insecta: Heteroptera: Helotrephidae) from Thailand and Vietnam, with descriptions of three new species. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, series B, 106: 67 - 80." type="journal article" year="2005">Zettel, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(five described species) is widely distributed from southern 
<collectingCountry id="F37B762B6A02FFCF033DFE10C9962BAE" box="[1124,1188,384,407]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">China</collectingCountry>
to Borneo (
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B4A6A02FFCF0275FE10C8842BAE" author="Zettel, H" box="[1324,1462,384,407]" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" pagination="67 - 80" refId="ref6180" refString="Zettel, H., 2005. Notes on the Helotrephini (Insecta: Heteroptera: Helotrephidae) from Thailand and Vietnam, with descriptions of three new species. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, series B, 106: 67 - 80." type="journal article" year="2005">Zettel, 2005</bibRefCitation>
), and possibly some species may be found in West 
<collectingCountry id="F37B762B6A02FFCF0239FE30C8F02B8E" box="[1376,1474,416,439]" name="Malaysia" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
in the future. Two further monotypic genera are known in the subfamily, but their presence in the study area is unlikely: 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D386A02FFCF041AFD90C9A5282E" authority="Papa" authorityName="Papa" box="[835,1175,512,535]" class="Insecta" family="Helotrephidae" genus="Trephotomas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compactus">
<emphasis id="B918EAA96A02FFCF041AFD90C964282E" box="[835,1110,512,535]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">Trephotomas compactus</emphasis>
Papá
</taxonomicName>
ek, Štys &amp; Tonner, 1988 has been recorded from southern 
<collectingCountry id="F37B762B6A02FFCF03F6FDB0C9C3280E" box="[1199,1265,544,567]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">China</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry id="F37B762B6A02FFCF0239FDB0C88D280E" box="[1376,1471,544,567]" name="Vietnam" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, northern and central 
<collectingCountry id="F37B762B6A02FFCF0340FDD0C948286E" box="[1049,1146,576,599]" name="Thailand" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">Thailand</collectingCountry>
; and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D386A02FFCF03F7FDD0CEF4284E" authority="Zettel, 2005" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Helotrephidae" genus="Papacekia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microphthalma">
<emphasis id="B918EAA96A02FFCF03F7FDD0C8F0286E" box="[1198,1474,576,599]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">Papacekia microphthalma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFD4B4A6A02FFCF041AFDF0CEF4284E" author="Zettel, H" box="[835,966,608,631]" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" pagination="67 - 80" refId="ref6180" refString="Zettel, H., 2005. Notes on the Helotrephini (Insecta: Heteroptera: Helotrephidae) from Thailand and Vietnam, with descriptions of three new species. Annalen des Naturhistorischen Museums in Wien, series B, 106: 67 - 80." type="journal article" year="2005">Zettel, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from Borneo. 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D386A02FFCF0330FDF0C810284E" box="[1129,1314,608,631]" class="Insecta" family="Helotrephidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Trephotomasinae">Trephotomasinae</taxonomicName>
possesses two unique characters, the pseudendocorium (
<figureCitation id="13572A3E6A02FFCF0257FD10C86C28AE" box="[1294,1374,640,663]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[114,158,1889,1910]" captionTargetBox="[116,1448,902,1863]" captionTargetId="figure-17@3.[81,1489,892,1871]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 12–24. Key characters of helotrephid genera. 12–14, Hemielytron in situ, dorsolateral aspect; cla = clavus, cls = claval suture, emb = embolium, pse = pseudendocorium, psm = pseudomembrane. (12) Platytrephes sitesi, hindwing-brachypterous morph, (13) Helotrephes australis, hindwing-brachypterous morph, and (14) Helotrephes australis, macropterous morph. 15–19, Cephalonotum (pnp = pronotal plate), lateral aspect, of (15) Helotrephes australis, (16) Distotrephes zetteli, hindwing-brachypterous morph, (17) Distotrephes pavelstysi Zettel, 1999, macropterous morph, (18) Tiphotrephes indicus, (19) Idiotrephes chinai. 20–23, Ventromedial carinae of thoracic and abdominal sternites, lateral aspect; prs – prosternum, mss – mesosternum, mts – metasternum, 2, 3, 4 etc. abdominal sternites 2, 3, 4 etc. (20) Helotrephes australis, (21) Ascetotrephes edmundsorum, (22) Hydrotrephes mixtus, (23) Hydrotrephes belomensis. 24, Metasternal carinae in Distotrephes zetteli, ventral aspect. Images not to scale." pageId="6" pageNumber="177">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) and the tarsal formula 2–2–3. The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D386A02FFCF03F0FD30C81D288E" authorityName="Zettel" authorityYear="2005" box="[1193,1327,672,695]" class="Insecta" family="Helotrephidae" genus="Platytrephes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B918EAA96A02FFCF03F0FD30C81D288E" box="[1193,1327,672,695]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="177">Platytrephes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can easily be recognized by its weakly convex and broad habitus (
<figureCitation id="13572A3E6A02FFCF0220FD50C88828EE" box="[1401,1466,704,727]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[137,181,2033,2054]" captionTargetBox="[166,1440,189,2008]" captionTargetId="figure-63@2.[165,1440,189,2008]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 1–11. 1–8, Habitus, dorsal aspect; 9–11, frontal aspect.(1) Fischerotrephes jaechi; (2) Platytrephes sitesi; (3, 9) Helotrephes rompinensis; (4, 11) Hydrotrephes benomensis; (5, 10) Ascetotrephes edmundsorum; (6) Idiotrephes chinai; (7) Distotrephes zetteli; (8) Tiphotrephes indicus. (© NHMW Hemiptera Image Collection; published with permission). Images not to scale." pageId="6" pageNumber="177">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) and wide, flattened medial areas on the metasternum and sternite 2. As far as their habitats are known, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D386A02FFCF0254FC90C8F0292E" box="[1293,1474,768,791]" class="Insecta" family="Helotrephidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Trephotomasinae">Trephotomasinae</taxonomicName>
is benthic on gravelly bottoms of clean streams.
</paragraph>
